<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-13T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/607</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-13T20:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            13, 1919, 8 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Please note and transmit to <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>:</p>
                            <p>Department is gratified to know that you feel willing to undertake
                                modified plan which has resulted from the negotiations at <pb facs="0357" n="307" xml:id="pg_307"/> Tokyo. It is believed that
                                Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName> has shown very
                                great tact and ability in reaching a frank and friendly
                                understanding with the Japanese Government and it is very much hoped
                                that you may now have an opportunity to reap some reward from your
                                own long and patient effort, also the men of the service corps.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_PF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>